    "- Explore relationships between charges and actual payments\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1.3 Understanding DRGs (Diagnosis Related Groups)\n",
    "\n",
    "### What are DRGs?\n",
    "DRGs are a patient classification system that groups hospital cases into categories based on:\n",
    "- **Primary diagnosis** (main reason for hospitalization)\n",
    "- **Procedures performed**\n",
    "- **Complications and comorbidities** (CC/MCC)\n",
    "- **Patient demographics** and discharge status\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why DRGs Matter\n",
    "1. **Payment System**: Medicare pays hospitals a predetermined amount per DRG\n",
    "2. **Resource Planning**: Hospitals use DRG data for staffing and budgeting\n",
    "3. **Quality Measurement**: DRG-specific outcomes indicate care quality\n",
    "4. **Policy Research**: DRG trends reveal changes in disease prevalence and treatment\n",
    "\n",
    "### Examples of Common DRGs\n",
    "- DRG 470: Major Hip & Knee Joint Replacement\n",
    "- DRG 871: Septicemia without Mechanical Ventilation  \n",
    "- DRG 291-293: Heart Failure & Shock\n",
    "- DRG 190-192: COPD (Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease)\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1.4 Research Questions This Dashboard Addresses\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Trend Analysis**: How have Medicare discharges and payments changed from 2013-2022?\n",
    "2. **Cost Variation**: Which procedures have the highest costs? Are costs increasing?\n",
    "3. **Volume Patterns**: What are the most common procedures? How has utilization changed?\n",
    "4. **Payment Analysis**: What's the relationship between submitted charges and actual Medicare payments?\n",
    "5. **Geographic Disparities**: How do costs and utilization vary across states?"
